<paragraph blockId="55.[264,1322,283,550]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName box="[430,685,444,469]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seqouensis">
<emphasis box="[430,685,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Ommatius seqouensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scarbrough &amp; Marascia" authorityYear="2003" box="[836,969,444,469]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectinus">
<emphasis box="[836,969,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">O. pectinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from congeners by the characters in the key, the smaller body, long yellow posteroventral bristles on the middle femur, and erect bristles on sternites 2­5.
</paragraph>
